41.Explain difference between  C and C++?

*C:
 It supports procedure oriented language.
 Virtual functions are not available.
 It doesnt support polymorphism.
 Exception handling features are not available in c.
 It follows top to bottom approach.
 .....

*C++:
 It supports object oriented language.
 virtual functions are available.
 It supports polymorphism.
 Exception handling features are available in c++.
 It follows bottom to top approach.


